Israeli Stocks: Delek Real Estate, IDB Holding, Koor, Maytronics

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-08-28T14:04:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-28/israeli-stocks-delek-real-estate-idb-holding-koor-maytronics.html
Israel â€™s TA-25 Index advanced 0.5
percent to 1,094.52 at the 4:30 p.m. close in Tel Aviv.
Investors traded about 603.9 million shekels ($168 million) of
shares and convertible securities today, according to Tel Aviv
Stock Exchange data.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Delek Real Estate Ltd. (DLKR)   jumped 11 percent to 0.22
shekel, the biggest gain since Aug. 14. The real-estate company
said bondholders agreed to a four-month delay in principal
payment on its series 25 debt after a 36 million-shekel
guarantee by the controlling shareholder.  IDB Holding Corp. (IDBH IT) dropped the most since Aug. 10,
declining 2.1 percent to 62.62 shekels. The  investment company 
reported a second-quarter loss of 1.3 billion shekels after net
income of 50 million shekels in the year-earlier period.  Jerusalem Economy (ECJM IT) increased 2.2 percent to 28.31
shekels, the most since Aug. 17. The company that leases office
and industrial space said second-quarter net income rose to 190
million shekels from 20 million shekels a year ago.  Koor Industries Ltd. (KOR)   plunged to the lowest on
record, falling 1.6 percent to 30.27 shekels. The holding
company reported a second-quarter loss of 1.93 billion shekels
after a profit of 35.4 million shekels a year earlier.  Maytronics Ltd. (MTRN)   rose to the highest level since
Aug. 4, advancing 3.1 percent to 2.412 shekels. The maker of
pool-cleaning equipment said second-quarter net income rose to
21 million shekels from 19 million shekels a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
